      • on

        public MiniJavaError on(int line,
               int column,
               java.lang.Object[] args)
        Factory method to create an actual error of this type.

        The slightly weird method name is because it feels kind of natural to do e.g:

        System.out.println(WRONG_RETURN_TYPE.on(line, column, type));

        Also, it's short :)

        Parameters:
        line - Line of the error.
        column - Column of the error.
        args - Arguments for the error message.
        Returns:
        The constructed MiniJavaError.
